        </p>
      </introduction>
          <task xml:id="exer_515a">
            <p>
              Calculate <m>1 + 3 + 5 + \cdots + \left( {2n - 1} \right)</m> for several 
              natural numbers <m>n</m>.
            </p>
          </task>
          <task xml:id="exer_515b">
            <statement>
            <p>
              Based on your work in <xref ref="exer_515a"/>, if <m>n \in \mathbb{N}</m>,
              make a conjecture about the value of the sum 
              <m>1 + 3 + 5 + \cdots + \left( {2n - 1} \right) = 
              \sum\limits_{j = 1}^n {\left( {2j - 1} \right)}</m>.
            </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
              <p>
                The conjecture is that  for each  <m>n \in \mathbb{N}</m>,  
                <m>1 + 3 + 5 + \cdots + (2n - 1) = n^2</m>.
              </p>
            </answer>
          </task>
          <task>
            <statement>
            <p>
              Use mathematical induction to prove your conjecture in <xref ref="exer_515b"/>.
            </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
              <p>
                The key to the inductive step is that
                <md>
                  <mrow>1 + 3 + 5 + \cdots + (2k - 1) \amp</mrow>
                  <mrow>+ (2(k+1) - 1)  \amp = \left[1 + 3 + 5 + \cdots + (2k - 1) \right] + (2(k+1) - 1)</mrow>
                  <mrow>\amp = k^2 + (2k + 1)</mrow>
                  <mrow>\amp = (k + 1)^2</mrow>
                </md>
              </p>
            </answer>
          </task>

